review_reply.reply_text:
Dear Mr. Irshad,
Greetings from Teethling Dental Care.
In all our treatment approaches, we go with the most conservative option. When we noticed that your wisdom tooth on the left side was causing cheek biting because of which you had developed an inflammatory response, the most conservative option was to do an enameloplasty which means only smoothening the sharp edge of the tooth. Your tooth in no way was chipped off. Unless the cause of the problem is eliminated, medication would only give you a symptomatic relief. We also prescribed you anti inflammatory medication for the swelling and advised warm salt water rinsing which is the ideal treatment protocol. We had also followed up with you to check if you were doing better, and you had responded positively. The treatment was also carried out only with your consent. Kindly let us know if there was any further clarification needed.
Regards,
Team - Teethling Dental Care.
